li
	h4.subtitle 2.2.4 - Sequence Viewer
	p PHYLOViZ Online also offers a way to visualize multiple alignments after node selection from the Tree, the <b><i>Sequence Viewer</i></b>, implememnted using the <a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/msa">BioJS MSA Viewer</a> package.
	br
	div(style="width:100%; text-align:center;")
		img(id="sequenceviewer1" href="/images/sequenceviewer1.png" style="width:40%; height: auto;" src="/images/sequenceviewer1.png")
	ul
		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="sequencefilter")
				h5 Filter
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="sequenceviewer5" href="/images/sequenceviewer5.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/sequenceviewer5.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p Filter the sequences or sequence positions you want to see by identity, treshold or by previous selection. Simply click on the <b><i>Filter</i></b> button on the upper-left side of the visualization.
		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="sequenceselect")
				h5 Select
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="sequenceviewer4" href="/images/sequenceviewer4.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/sequenceviewer4.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p Explore and select the sequences by searching for a specific motif. This can be done in the <b><i>Selection</i></b> button on the upper-left side of the visualization. Selection can also be made by clicking on the name or id of each sequence.
		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="sequencecolour")
				h5 Colour
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="sequenceviewer2" href="/images/sequenceviewer2.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/sequenceviewer2.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p Change the colour of the visual representation according to sequence characteristics. To do that, click on the <b><i>Color scheme</i></b> button on the upper-left side of the visualization.

		li
			div.tutorialsubsections(id="sequenceorder")
				h5 Order
				table
					tr.subrow
						td.tutorialcolumns
							img(id="sequenceviewer3" href="/images/sequenceviewer3.png" style="width:60%; height: auto;" src="/images/sequenceviewer3.png")
						td.othercolumns
							<span class="glyphicon glyphicon-arrow-right"></span>
						td(style="text-align:justify")
							p Order the entries according to characteristics of sequences, such as their labels and identity. To do that, click on the <b><i>Order</i></b> button on the upper-left side of the visualization.


